content:
Most of the courses recommend switching to coding, but many people don’t have the foundation and conditions. So I’ll talk about two blue-collar high-paying jobs that everyone ignores.
The first is Chinese chef, a long-established and stable job, and chefs never lose their jobs.
Manicurist, this is really a high-paying job in Italy, with a starting salary of 3,500 euros.
There is no age limit for these two jobs. If you are old, don’t know the language, don’t have a degree, and want to come out, it’s actually a good idea to start with these jobs.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Of course, some people will say, "Aren't you asking them to be cheated by the Chinese boss?" I mean, if you are old, don't know the language, and don't have a degree, you can at least gain a foothold in a foreign country and accumulate your first pot of gold with such skills.
If you don't have a fantasy, don't always fantasize about moving a chair and working in a big company. Unless you are better than the locals, why don't they want you instead of the locals?
